1.  What is NextJS? And why we use it over ReactJS?
A.  1️⃣  What is Next.js?
    Next.js is a React framework used to build modern web applications.
    It is built on top of ReactJS
    It extends React by providing built-in features and project structure.
    Helps developers build scalable and optimized applications.
    👉 In simple terms:
    React = UI Library
    Next.js = Framework built on React
    React helps create UI components, while Next.js provides complete application architecture.
    
    2️⃣ Why Use Next.js Instead of React?
    When using React alone, developers must install and configure many libraries manually.
    Example in React:
    🔹Routing → npm i react-router-dom
    🔹Build tools → npm i webpack
    🔹SEO handling
    🔹Performance optimization
    🔹API handling
    🔹Next.js already provides many of these features out of the box.

    3️⃣ Built-in Features of Next.js
    1. File-Based Routing
    Routing is automatically handled by the file structure.
    Example-> app/about/page.tsx
    This automatically creates the route:
    /about
    No need for react-router-dom.

    2. Server-Side Rendering (SSR)
    Next.js can render pages on the server before sending them to the browser.
    Flow:
    Server → Render HTML → Send to Browser
    Benefits:
    🔹Better SEO
    🔹Faster first page load
    🔹Better performance

    3. Built-in Optimization
    Next.js automatically optimizes many things:
    🔹Image optimization ->
    ReactJS - 
    No automatic resizing.
    No modern formats. [ Original → PNG/JPG/JPEG ].
    No lazy loading by default. [ All Images in one go ].
    NextJS -
    Automatic Resizing - [ Desktop → 1000px, Tablet → 600px, Mobile → 300px ].
    Next.js converts images. [ Served → WebP/AVIF (smaller size) ]. Result → faster loading.
    Images outside the viewport are not loaded until the user scrolls. This improves page speed.
    🔹Code splitting -> 
    ReactJS- [ Implement manually ]
    const Page = React.lazy(() => import("./Page"));
    NextJS -
    When a user visits /about, only the about code loads.
    🔹Font optimization
    🔹Caching
    🔹Faster page loading
    Example optimized image component:
    import Image from "next/image";
    <Image src="/profile.png" width={500} height={500} alt="Picture of the author" />

    4. Middleware
    Middleware allows code to run before a request is completed. It runs between the user request and the server response.
    Ex - User → /dashboard
           ↓
         Middleware checks token
           ↓
         No token → redirect to /login
         Has token → allow access
    Common uses:
    🔹Authentication
    🔹Redirect users
    🔹Logging
    🔹Security checks

    5. CSS Support
    Next.js supports multiple styling methods without configuration.
    Supported options:
    🔹CSS
    🔹CSS Modules
    🔹Sass
    🔹Tailwind CSS
    🔹Styled Components

    4️⃣ Next.js Can Be Full-Stack - 
    Next.js allows building frontend and backend in the same project.
    You can create APIs inside the project.
    Example structure-> app/api/users/route.ts
    API URL-> /api/users

    5️⃣ Benefits of Next.js
    🔹Faster development
    🔹Built-in routing
    🔹Better SEO
    🔹Automatic optimization
    🔹Backend API support
    🔹Scalable architecture



